title: Measurement and analysis of alpha particle induced reactions on gold.

x4freetext: Measurement and analysis of alpha particle induced
reactions on gold.

x4codes.hlp: M.S. University of Baroda, Baroda, India

x4freetext: Physics department
School of studies in Physics.

x4codes.hlp: Variable Energy Cyclotron Centre, Kolkata, India

x4freetext: Spectroscopically pure gold foils of purity greater
than 99.99% and thickness 24-mg/cm**2 were used as
targets in the stacks together with aluminum degraders
of varying thicknesses to reduce the beam energy to
desired level.
Copper foils of thicknesses 23-mg/cm**2 and
8.9-mg/cm**2 were used as flux monitor.
HYBRID and INDEX models.

x4codes.hlp: Variable Energy Cyclotron Centre, Kolkata, India

x4freetext: The beam current on used targets were kept of
the order of 250 nanoamperes.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Journal of Inorganic and Nuclear Chemistry, Vol.36, p.3647 (1974)

x4freetext: The total error in the experimental cross
section is contributed by:
error in the photopeak areas,     1-4%
error indetector efficiency       3-4%,
uniformity of the foil thickness  1-2%,
error in spectroscopic data       1-7%
standard deviation 10% of the monitor cross
section from which the flux is deduced.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The relative errors which affect the shape
of the excitation functions is about 6%
